reply.question: 6. If the app shares data with third parties, what third parties does the app share data with?

answer.full_answer: The app shares data with vendors, health care providers, and other entities as necessary to provide services and improve products.

reply.analysis: The privacy policy mentions that data can be disclosed to vendors, health care providers, and other entities to support services and enhance products.
reply.reference: We will use and disclose the information we receive from and about you to provide you with access to the Platform and to improve our products and services in accordance with applicable law. For example, we may disclose the information to our vendors so they can provide their services to us, including (i) verifying your identification during the registration process, and (ii) processing payments for selected treatment options. We may also disclose information to your health care provider who accesses the platform as part of their services. URL: https://www.pmnowapp.com/pm-now-user-privacy-policy
